			<div class="post" id="post-12849">
				<h2><a href="http://www.amerivestllc.com/Global_Finance_Blog/?p=12849" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Russell:  UK Should End Recession in Second Half on Global Uptick">Russell:  UK Should End Recession in Second Half on Global Uptick</a></h2>
				<small>February 12th, 2013 <!-- by Amerivest Advisory Board Contributors --></small>

				<div class="entry">
					<div class="KonaFilter"><p><span><em>Written by <a rel="author" href="http://econintersect.com/authors/author_rel.htm?author=/home/aleta/public_html/authors/j_lounsbury.htm" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','econintersect.com']);">John Lounsbury</a></em></span></p>
<p><span>Russell Investments has issued a white paper, the <a href="http://www.russell.com/documents/uk/about-russell/russell-investments-global-outlook-2013.pdf" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','download','www.russell.com/documents/uk/about-russell/russell-investments-global-outlook-2013.pdf']);">2013 Global Market Outlook</a>,&#160; which foresees moderate growth in the U.S. and China along with episodes of European-generated volatility.&#160; A report for the <a href="http://wire.russell.com/2013/01/25/the-united-kingdom-treading-water/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','wire.russell.com']);">UK outlook</a> by Wouter Sturkenboom sees Great Britain treading water but doing better in the second half of the year.&#160; Sturkenboom says that since the Great Financial Crisis (GFC) the UK &#8220;<em>has  been paying the price for its pre-2008 private and public sector debt buildup</em>.&#8221;&#160; Although Sturkenboom does not see the UK policy mix changing materially in the coming year, he does foresee the uptick in the second half of 2013 producing growth of 1-1.5% for the entire twelve months.</span></p>
<p><span><img src="http://econintersect.com/images/2013/2/99633058stockoutlookRussellSturkenboomEMEAvideo.JPG" alt="RussellSturkenboomEMEAvideo" width="378" height="215" /></span></p>
<p><span><span>[<em>Video can be viewed at end of article</em>.]</span><br /></span></p>
<p><a href="http://econintersect.com/b2evolution/blog3.php/2013/02/12/russell-uk-should-end-recession-in-second-half-on-global-uptick#more5764" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','econintersect.com']);">Read more &raquo;</a><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/GlobalEconomicIntersection-Markets/~4/kmwo_wllrVI" height="1" width="1" /> <!--END--></p>
</div><script type="text/javascript" class="owbutton" src="http://www.onlywire.com/btn/button_
97442" title="Russell:  UK Should End Recession in Second Half on Global Uptick" url="http://www.amerivestllc.com/Global_Finance_Blog/?p=12849"></script>				</div>

